result.notes: The property interests of Norfolk County Council are represented as polygons, points and lines. Each site has an identifier (UPRN) which provides a unique link to further detail of NCC property database held on the NPS Connect2 property database. The data and information are static information updated periodically. Up to date information should be obtained before being used. The sites represent land or buildings or services being provided from a privately owned asset e.g. church schools. Further information can be provided from the data supplier.
